==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Suckling
<hw>Suck"ling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>sokeling</ets>. See <er>Suck</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A young child or animal nursed at the breast.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A small kind of yellow clover (<spn>Trifolium
filiforme</spn>) common in Southern Europe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sucrate</ent>⟦br⟧
